-Okay.

01:35.200 --> 01:37.167
Is this your car?
-My grandma's car...

01:37.200 --> 01:39.833
Your grandma's car?
Okay. Where y'all headed?

01:39.867 --> 01:42.367
-I'm goin' to pick
my grandma up. I'm just goin'
to pick my grandma up

01:42.400 --> 01:44.967
after this.
-Okay. Anything illegal
in the car?

01:45.067 --> 01:47.267
-No, sir.
-Would you have a problem
if I searched the car?

01:47.300 --> 01:50.433
-The car, uh, oh, go ahead.
-No, it's up to you. I mean...

01:50.467 --> 01:53.067
-(mutters)... No.
-You don't want me to?

01:53.067 --> 01:55.067
Okay, fair enough.
What's your name?

01:55.067 --> 01:58.900
-Me? He got it.
-Okay, I'm askin' your name.

01:58.933 --> 02:02.333
-He got my ID.
-Okay, I just asked
for your name.

02:02.367 --> 02:05.433
-We can go that route, too.
-What route?

02:05.467 --> 02:09.067
-Just got a hit.
Let me get you to step
out of the car? Leave him in.

02:09.067 --> 02:11.633
One at a time.
Step out of the car.

02:11.667 --> 02:13.933
-What am I gettin' out for?
-'Cause I can smell
the odor of marijuana

02:13.967 --> 02:16.300
comin' from the vehicle.
-There's no marijuana
in this vehicle, sir.

02:16.333 --> 02:20.600
-Okay, I can smell it,
so it's either on you--
Turn around.

02:20.633 --> 02:24.833
Step back off the car.
Spread your legs.

02:24.867 --> 02:28.467
Don't... don't move.
You hear me?

02:28.500 --> 02:33.400
Anything? Zero.
Don't let him out.
He's gonna try to get out.

02:33.433 --> 02:35.800
Three-eight, give me traffic,
one more unit.

02:35.833 --> 02:38.667
-Brown: Stay in the car.
-(police radio chatters)

02:38.700 --> 02:40.200
-Put your hands
behind your back.

02:40.233 --> 02:41.300
-Do not reach around.
-Hey!

02:41.333 --> 02:42.767
-Put your hands on the dash!

02:42.800 --> 02:44.400
Put your hands on the dash.

02:44.433 --> 02:47.100
-You understand me?
-Three-eight, have 'em
step it up.

02:47.133 --> 02:49.467
-I'm tellin' you right now,
if you take your hands
off the dash--

02:49.500 --> 02:52.133
-'Cause you got a gun
in your waistband,
your partner's in there

02:52.167 --> 02:56.267
reachin' around.
I'm gonna stay alive today,
do you understand?

02:56.300 --> 02:58.600
-Hey, I'm not even resistin',
why you gotta go so high
with it?

02:58.633 --> 03:01.833
-That way in case you wanna
get silly.

03:01.867 --> 03:04.400
Sir, don't-- it'd be
in your best interests
not to be pullin' your hands

03:04.433 --> 03:06.500
off that dash.
You understand?

03:06.533 --> 03:08.833
Deputy Brown:
I'm tellin' you,
I'm watchin' you.

03:08.867 --> 03:10.833
-Three-eight, one detained.
You got him?

03:10.867 --> 03:13.900
Back up and lay on your face.
Back up and lay on your face.

03:13.933 --> 03:16.767
-I get arrested, too?
-No, you're goin' in custody
until we figure out

03:16.800 --> 03:19.700
what else we got here.
You got anything on you?
-No, sir.

03:19.733 --> 03:22.600
-Pulled a car over
that rolled a stop sign
back here on Clifton.

03:22.633 --> 03:26.300
Um, driver's extremely nervous.
I'm gettin' the smell, odor
of marijuana

03:26.333 --> 03:30.067
comin' from the vehicle.
Pulled the driver out,
and immediately noticed

03:30.100 --> 03:32.433
this tucked in his waistband
in the small of his back.

03:32.467 --> 03:35.600
-(indistinct)
-Turn this way.
What have you got

03:35.633 --> 03:38.833
in your pants?
He's got weed.

03:38.867 --> 03:42.067
-(police radio chatters)

03:43.300 --> 03:44.967
-Due to the quantity
of narcotics,

03:45.067 --> 03:47.367
we'll be seizin' the money.
-I didn't even run no stop sign.

03:47.400 --> 03:49.067
-You did.
-I made a right.

03:49.067 --> 03:50.533
-You ran a stop sign.
-No, I didn't.

03:50.567 --> 03:53.533
-Turn around.
That's the least
of your worries, okay?

03:53.567 --> 03:56.433
I pull you out, you're a little
fidgety, kind of nervous.
-By the way you pulled me

03:56.467 --> 03:59.200
out of the car.
You jacked me up, like...
-You had a gun.

03:59.233 --> 04:01.433
-If I want-- What was I
was gonna do with it?
You seen-- you had--

04:01.467 --> 04:03.067
-I don't know.
I don't know. Listen...

04:03.100 --> 04:05.967
-Did you feel a threat?
Was there a capability?
Was there intent?

04:06.067 --> 04:08.867
-Yeah. You had the ability.
-That's a deadly force triangle,
you know what that is?

04:08.900 --> 04:10.933
-What's that?
-A deadly force triangle,
you know what that is?

04:10.967 --> 04:13.667
-What's a deadly--
-Capability, intent,
opportunity, did I have

04:13.700 --> 04:17.667
any of that?
I had the capability,
but di-- but, but, but

04:17.700 --> 04:20.467
did I intend to?
-I don't know your intentions,
so I can't say you--

04:20.500 --> 04:23.067
whether you did
or you didn't. I have no clue
of your intentions.

04:23.100 --> 04:26.733
Did you know my intentions?
-No, 'cause I ain't do nothin'.

04:26.767 --> 04:29.533
-So, if you don't know mine,
how am I supposed to know yours?

04:29.567 --> 04:32.300
Right?
-I was bein' cooperative.

04:32.333 --> 04:34.167
-But you had a gun
in your waistband.

04:34.200 --> 04:37.600
-For my safety, for real.
-Okay. Mine's for my safety,
but I don't know

04:37.633 --> 04:40.067
your intentions.
So I have to take
all precautions,

04:40.100 --> 04:42.167
to make sure I stay alive.
-All right.

04:42.200 --> 04:43.600
-Agree?
-I agree with that.

04:43.633 --> 04:45.567
-I wanna go home to my family
just like you do, brother.

04:45.600 --> 04:48.733
Okay? Fair enough.
-All right.

04:48.767 --> 04:53.167
-Josh, right?
-I, I, I w-wish I could,
so I could tell y'all,

04:53.200 --> 04:57.400
so he could go to prison
for life. He's-- he killed
my homeboy. Yes, sir, that's me.

04:57.433 --> 04:59.600
-Okay, I didn't see
your glasses. Turn and talk
to me for a second.

04:59.633 --> 05:01.867
You understand your rights, sir,
I read you your rights?
-Yes, sir.

05:01.900 --> 05:03.733
-What's goin' on
with your homeboy?
-I don't know.

05:03.767 --> 05:05.567
-Did you know he had the weed
in the car?

05:05.600 --> 05:09.133
You couldn't smell it?
-I wouldn't know... I, my
nose's stopped up,

05:09.167 --> 05:11.233
I got a-- I just really
gettin' over a cold.

05:11.267 --> 05:13.200
-Okay. What about the gun?

05:13.233 --> 05:15.733
-I didn't know nothin'
about the gun. Like I say,
he just picked me up.

05:15.767 --> 05:17.667
-Okay. Are you
a convicted felon?

05:17.700 --> 05:20.067
-I'm on probation.
-For what?

05:20.067 --> 05:23.067
-For marijuana possession.
-Under or over?

05:23.067 --> 05:24.900
-Over.
-Oh, okay.

05:24.933 --> 05:26.833
So you know bein' in the
presence of all this could...

05:26.867 --> 05:28.567
-Yes, sir, I know.
-...possibly violate...

05:28.600 --> 05:30.767
-That's why I said--
I'm lettin' you know
I didn't know it was there.

05:30.800 --> 05:33.300
-All right, well, sit tight,
and once we get things
sorted out, we'll get you

05:33.333 --> 05:34.433
cut loose.
-All right.

05:34.467 --> 05:36.300
-All right?

05:36.333 --> 05:39.600
Damian, why do you have the gun?
-For safety, too many people

05:39.633 --> 05:42.200
are gettin' killed.
-I can... completely agree
with you on that.

05:42.233 --> 05:44.767
Are you a convicted felon?
-No, I'm not, I'm none of that.

05:44.800 --> 05:47.667
-Where'd you get the gun?
-I bought that.

05:47.700 --> 05:49.867
-And how much
did you pay for it?
-200.

05:49.900 --> 05:51.233
-200?
-Yeah.

05:51.267 --> 05:53.367
-It's a pretty nice gun.
Taurus was a--
was like a PT-111?

05:53.400 --> 05:57.067
-Yeah.
-Pretty nice gun.
Got one myself.

05:57.067 --> 06:00.133
You think $200
is a reasonable price for that?

06:00.167 --> 06:05.100
Knowin' they're probably
more than that?
-I mean...

06:05.133 --> 06:07.900
-Pretty cheap.
-Yeah. I know
they're like 699 for it.

06:07.933 --> 06:11.867
-Yeah, so if somebody
come and offer me
a PT-111 for $200,

06:11.900 --> 06:15.467
and-- like they did you,
what, what was, probably
the first thing

06:15.500 --> 06:17.833
that popped into your head?
Be honest.
-I need it.

06:17.867 --> 06:20.867
-And what?
Probably stolen.

06:20.900 --> 06:23.233
For 200 bucks, it is
what it is.
-Right.

06:23.267 --> 06:24.867
-You know what I mean?
-Yeah.

06:24.900 --> 06:26.433
-It probably crossed
your mind.
-He had a box

06:26.467 --> 06:29.300
and everything with it.
-Okay. Well,
the gun's stolen.

06:29.333 --> 06:33.167
-Is it?
-It is. So, possession
of a stolen firearm

06:33.200 --> 06:36.067
during the commission
of a felony. Marijuana's
a felony amount.

06:36.067 --> 06:38.733
Okay? Were you fixin'
to go get rid
of that weed, or...

06:38.767 --> 06:41.133
-Yeah, I was gonna pick up
my grandma, actually.

06:41.167 --> 06:43.133
-Okay... and then go,
try to make
a couple dollars?

06:43.167 --> 06:46.667
-Right.
-Okay. Well, sit tight for me,
give me just a second.

06:46.700 --> 06:49.067
I'll be right back
over here. All right.

06:49.067 --> 06:52.267
The driver admitted
it was stolen. He said
it's his, and he bought it

06:52.300 --> 06:55.900
for $200. Said he wanted it
for protection.
-Well... around here

06:55.933 --> 06:57.767
you need it, but...
-Yeah. I know,
that being said, he--

06:57.800 --> 06:59.600
-Gotta do it
the right way.
-Yeah, he takes the ride,

06:59.633 --> 07:02.233
and a successful--
stolen gun taken off
the streets.

07:04.333 --> 07:07.067
-I love my job.
I love comin' to work,
I love gettin'

07:07.067 --> 07:09.400
to serve the community
and, and interact
with different people,

07:09.433 --> 07:12.067
and the aspect of never knowing
what's gonna happen next.

07:12.067 --> 07:13.867
But it's definitely nice
when I'm able to go home.

07:13.900 --> 07:17.167
I've got my wife and my kids
there, and I like to spend
a lot of time with them,

07:17.200 --> 07:18.500
and have as much fun
as we can,

07:18.533 --> 07:21.067
and, and leave work at work.

07:21.067 --> 07:22.833
Got a vehicle rollin'
through the neighborhood,

07:22.867 --> 07:25.200
stayin' off
the main streets,
that didn't use its blinker.

07:25.233 --> 07:27.067
We're gonna pull him over
and talk to him
for a second.

07:27.067 --> 07:28.200
(siren)

07:28.233 --> 07:29.967
(indistinct)

07:30.067 --> 07:31.567
451, Code 58.

07:31.600 --> 07:34.067
-(radio) 451, go ahead.
-Maroon Camaro.

07:34.067 --> 07:37.367
-(radio chatter)
-(indistinct)

07:45.367 --> 07:49.300
-Reason I was stoppin' you
is 'cause you didn't
use your blinker back there.

07:49.333 --> 07:51.767
-I just live right here.
-I understand that,
but when the police

07:51.800 --> 07:54.467
start pullin' you over,
you pull over, you don't keep
drivin' home.

07:54.500 --> 07:56.600
Do you have warrants
or somethin'?
-No...

07:56.633 --> 07:59.500
-Is there somethin' goin' on
of why you wouldn't--
why you wouldn't pull over?

07:59.533 --> 08:02.267
-I don't have insurance.
-Okay, well, whether
you pull over here

08:02.300 --> 08:05.500
or pull over there,
you still don't have insurance,
so go ahead and pull over, okay?

08:05.533 --> 08:07.867
All right, let me get
your license and insurance,
okay? Or your license.

08:07.900 --> 08:10.700
-I don't have a license.
-You don't have any kind
of-- do you have any kind

08:10.733 --> 08:13.100
of Texas ID on you?
-I'm fightin' with my--
with my fiancé...

08:13.133 --> 08:14.700
-Is he here?
-Yes.

08:14.733 --> 08:18.067
-Go ahead and step out for me.
Is this car registered
to you, ma'am?

08:18.067 --> 08:20.133
-Yes.
-Okay.

08:20.167 --> 08:23.233
Go ahead and step back here
in front of my car.

08:23.267 --> 08:26.600
-In front of your car.
-Yeah, just right here.

08:28.733 --> 08:30.700
You have anything on you
that I need to know about?

08:30.733 --> 08:32.533
John:
Thank you. We're done.
Are you happy?

08:32.567 --> 08:34.700
-Is this your boyfriend
back here?
-I work at Denny's.

08:34.733 --> 08:37.500
-Hey, sir, go ahead
and wait inside for me, okay?

08:37.533 --> 08:39.767
You don't need to come
over here.
-You got it.

08:39.800 --> 08:44.333
-He's just been really bad,
disrespecting me, and I work
graveyards at Denny's.

08:44.367 --> 08:50.067
-Mm-hm. And tomorrow's
Mother's Day, so I met
my, my daughter, and we were...

08:50.067 --> 08:52.633
we'd already been fighting,
so that's why I left.

08:52.667 --> 08:54.467
He told me to
go get some sleep,

08:54.500 --> 08:56.867
and he started calling me
a stupid bitch.

08:56.900 --> 09:00.200
And he stuck a White Castle
scorching hot hamburger
in my mouth

09:00.233 --> 09:02.133
while I was laying in the bed.

09:02.167 --> 09:03.767
And I told him I didn't want it,

09:03.800 --> 09:05.633
because I had this
cut on my lip.

09:05.667 --> 09:08.167
And he did it anyway,
and he just--

09:08.200 --> 09:09.800
He constantly disagrees with me

09:09.833 --> 09:12.300
and makes me do things
that I don't want to.

09:12.333 --> 09:13.867
So I just--
-So...

09:13.900 --> 09:15.667
what's his issue
with doing stuff like that?

09:15.700 --> 09:17.933
Kind of irrational.
Is he-- Is he on drugs?

09:17.967 --> 09:20.167
-No, he's just been
trying to control me.

09:20.200 --> 09:21.767
-This is your house, correct?
-Yes.

09:21.800 --> 09:23.733
-And you don't have access
to get into the house
if it's locked?

09:23.767 --> 09:25.767
-But I have money,
I could go to a hotel.

09:25.800 --> 09:28.733
-Well, and here's the thing,
we'll get to all that
in a minute.

09:28.767 --> 09:30.800
We would like to talk to him and
make sure of what's going on,

09:30.833 --> 09:32.933
and then go from there.

09:32.967 --> 09:34.633
-(knocking)

09:34.667 --> 09:36.300
-Come open the door,
talk to us.

09:36.333 --> 09:38.467
-We're just wanting to make sure
that all it was was an argument,

09:38.500 --> 09:39.833
but I need to talk to you, too.

09:39.867 --> 09:41.433
-I have warrants out
for my arrest.

09:41.467 --> 09:42.733
You gonna arrest me?

09:42.767 --> 09:44.767
-Okay, well we're gonna
have to get that figured out.

09:44.800 --> 09:46.467
That's a possibility,
but I need to talk to you,

09:46.500 --> 09:48.367
and she needs access
to her house.

09:48.400 --> 09:51.067
-I'll give her access,
but do we have to

09:51.067 --> 09:52.633
be arrested today?

09:52.667 --> 09:54.300
Uh, let me call my boss.

09:54.333 --> 09:56.400
Let me get some bondsman
worked up.

09:56.433 --> 09:57.933
-Okay. Come out here
and talk to us,

09:57.967 --> 09:59.067
and we can figure all that out.

09:59.067 --> 10:01.033
-I got a seatbelt problem.

10:01.067 --> 10:03.900
Thank you, Carrie. Thank you.
-(dog barking)

10:05.667 --> 10:07.700
-Come here.
-Okay. Go ahead
and step out here for us.

10:07.733 --> 10:10.367
-You're not gonna
arrest me like--
-Come out here and talk to us.

10:10.400 --> 10:12.600
-You're not gonna put, like,
handcuffs on me.
-Step out here, John.

10:12.633 --> 10:14.400
-Yes. That's what
arrest is, okay?

10:14.433 --> 10:16.633
-Come here, John.
-I have a dislocated shoulder.

10:16.667 --> 10:18.200
-Okay. That's fine.
-Thank you, Carrie.

10:18.233 --> 10:20.733
-John, step out here for us.

10:20.767 --> 10:22.433
-Thank you, Carrie.
-Sir.

10:22.467 --> 10:24.833
-I didn't do anything.
-We are here to make sure
there are no more disputes,

10:24.867 --> 10:26.400
not to keep having
a further one.

10:26.433 --> 10:27.700
So step out here.

10:27.733 --> 10:29.133
Set that down right here for us.

10:29.167 --> 10:30.567
-Okay.
-Get your hand
out of your pocket,

10:30.600 --> 10:32.667
and step out here.
-Come out here right now.

10:32.700 --> 10:34.400
-Okay--
-You can step out here,
or we're gonna have--

10:34.433 --> 10:35.867
-Carrie: No, babe!

10:35.900 --> 10:37.500
-Come out here.
-Don't hurt me.

10:37.533 --> 10:39.367
-I'm not here to hurt you.
-I got a dislocated shoulder.

10:39.400 --> 10:41.300
-But we need you to listen
and do what you're told. Okay?

10:41.333 --> 10:43.333
-Don't do this one.
-I have to do this one.

10:43.367 --> 10:45.400
I need you to relax,
'cause then that's what will
make it okay.

10:45.433 --> 10:47.800
-Carrie. Carrie. Carrie.
-You're doing this.
You did this.

10:47.833 --> 10:49.200
-Why don't you quit drinking?

10:49.233 --> 10:52.167
Please sleep.
I'm gonna sleep tonight.

10:52.200 --> 10:54.533
I'm glad you're proud.

10:54.567 --> 10:56.633
I'm glad you're proud, girl.
-Hey, hey.

10:56.667 --> 10:58.667
Listen-- Listen to me.
-We're not getting married.

10:58.700 --> 11:01.500
-John, listen to me. Stop.
-You blew it! You blew it!

11:01.533 --> 11:02.800
-Stop. Okay, let's go
to the car.

11:02.833 --> 11:05.133
-Yeah, it's over.
-All the money that I paid...

11:05.167 --> 11:06.800
-It ain't about money, Carrie.

11:06.833 --> 11:08.667
-It is, 'cause I worked
my ass off!

11:08.700 --> 11:10.533
-You can have it all!
We're done!

11:10.567 --> 11:12.167
