(radio chatter)

14:13.400 --> 14:15.267
-Hi. How you doing?
-Good. How are you?

14:15.300 --> 14:16.967
-Pretty good.
-(music playing from radio)

14:17.067 --> 14:19.733
-I'm Officer McFarland.
You have your license
and insurance with you?

14:19.767 --> 14:21.333
The reason you're
being pulled over is,

14:21.367 --> 14:22.400
there's a few things.
-Okay.

14:22.433 --> 14:23.667
-You didn't change la--

14:23.700 --> 14:25.333
You didn't use your signal
when you changed lanes.

14:25.367 --> 14:27.267
You kind of rolled the stop sign
as it was turning red,

14:27.300 --> 14:28.933
the light back there.
-That sucks.

14:28.967 --> 14:30.467
-All kinds of stuff.
You in a hurry or what?

14:30.500 --> 14:32.600
-No, sir. Just write my tickets.

14:32.633 --> 14:34.333
I apologize, sincerely.

14:34.367 --> 14:36.100
-Okay. I'm not here to
necessarily write you tickets.

14:36.133 --> 14:38.400
I'm just trying to figure out
if you're in a hurry
or what's going on.

14:38.433 --> 14:40.267
-Oh, no, actually, um,
I mean. You know what, dude?

14:40.300 --> 14:41.467
I'm gonna be honest with you.

14:41.500 --> 14:43.233
I just got out of
a four-year relationship.

14:43.267 --> 14:44.700
-Mm-hmm.
-Um...

14:44.733 --> 14:47.233
I met the girl while I was at
Neal Unit Prison.

14:47.267 --> 14:49.700
I just got out June 26th
of last year.

14:49.733 --> 14:54.067
Um... I didn't--
I didn't, uh...

14:54.067 --> 14:55.833
Man, I took advantage
of this girl.

14:55.867 --> 14:58.433
I didn't-- I didn't
hold her hand in public,
this and that.

14:58.467 --> 15:00.600
And, uh, there's just
so much more to it.

15:00.633 --> 15:02.367
Um, dude,

15:02.400 --> 15:04.767
I don't even know
who I just bought this beer for.

15:04.800 --> 15:07.267
But, like, lately, I'm just
trying to, like,

15:07.300 --> 15:09.133
help out any kind
of person possible,

15:09.167 --> 15:11.533
because I feel wrong
for the things that I've done,

15:11.567 --> 15:13.167
and I just wanna make up for it.

15:13.200 --> 15:14.800
-You must have done her
real bad, man. It's got--

15:14.833 --> 15:17.067
-I really did, because
this girl just let her kids

15:17.067 --> 15:19.533
get, uh, CPS took her kids.
-Mmm.

15:19.567 --> 15:21.667
-Uh, no (bleep), man. Um--
-Okay.

15:21.700 --> 15:23.733
Man, I'm gonna be
honest with you.
I don't have insurance.

15:23.767 --> 15:25.367
If you wanna write me a ticket,
you can.

15:25.400 --> 15:28.933
-Okay.
-I'm actually dropping
this beer off to this woman.

15:28.967 --> 15:30.467
-But you don't know
who you bought it for?

15:30.500 --> 15:32.633
-No, sir. Hey, as sad
as this sounds,

15:32.667 --> 15:34.067
and I might look
like a bitch, dude,

15:34.067 --> 15:35.733
and you might think I'm weak.
-Nah.

15:35.767 --> 15:39.267
-Like, ever since this past
two weeks since I broke up
with this girl,

15:39.300 --> 15:42.067
man, I've been--
Like, I'll stop at a store,

15:42.067 --> 15:44.800
and I'll just look around,
or I'm just looking around
while I'm driving

15:44.833 --> 15:47.367
just to see if anybody needs
some kind of help, dude,

15:47.400 --> 15:50.067
because, like,
I've been selfish, and...

15:50.100 --> 15:51.667
and, uh, man.

15:51.700 --> 15:53.467
-Nothing wrong
with helping people, man.

15:53.500 --> 15:55.667
-And, hey, look, I'm probably,
like, uh,

15:55.700 --> 15:58.067
contributing to this woman's
addiction or whatever,

15:58.067 --> 16:00.300
but I just wanna make up
for things I've paid.

16:00.333 --> 16:02.100
-Is there anything in the car
we need to know about?

16:02.133 --> 16:03.833
-Uh, there's a beer.
-Well, I'm not worried.

16:03.867 --> 16:06.267
It's closed, man.
You already showed me that part.
I'm not worried about that.

16:06.300 --> 16:07.767
-But you can come
search the car.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.567
I'll get out, dude.
I don't have anything to hide.

16:09.600 --> 16:12.300
-Okay. Go ahead and step out
for me, then, if you don't mind
us searching it.

16:12.333 --> 16:14.800
And I'll have you
stand back here with my partner
for just a second, okay?

16:14.833 --> 16:16.567
-That's fine.
-You don't have any warrants
or nothing?

16:16.600 --> 16:18.933
-No, dude.
-Haven't caught any other
charges since you got out?

16:18.967 --> 16:20.733
-No, man, I'm worki--
-Step right back here.

16:20.767 --> 16:22.467
-I'm, like, just trying
to change my life, dude.

16:22.500 --> 16:24.067
-Just stand right here
in front of the car.

16:24.067 --> 16:26.200
If you could put your hands
up on the hood
for just a second, okay?

16:26.233 --> 16:27.700
-You got anything on you?
-No, sir.

16:27.733 --> 16:29.667
-Can I search you?
-Yeah, that's fine, dude.

16:29.700 --> 16:31.733
-You said, "no"
on warrants, huh?
-No, sir.

16:31.767 --> 16:33.533
What were you in for,
if you don't mind me asking?

16:33.567 --> 16:35.333
-Aggravated assault
on a public servant.

16:35.367 --> 16:36.700
-Well, there you go.

16:36.733 --> 16:38.967
-I was young, I was 21.

16:39.067 --> 16:40.467
-Hey, we all make mistakes, bud.

16:40.500 --> 16:42.267
-Hang tight with my partner
for just a second, okay?

16:42.300 --> 16:43.933
You can smoke your cigarette
or whatever.

16:43.967 --> 16:45.267
-So what's the deal
with your girl?

16:45.300 --> 16:46.667
-Oh, she's not my girlfriend.
I mean,

16:46.700 --> 16:48.167
I met her while
I was at Neal Unit.

16:48.200 --> 16:50.700
I was in prison, and we have
a wonderful story.

16:50.733 --> 16:53.100
Because, like, you don't see
nothing like that.

16:53.133 --> 16:54.733
There's so much stuff
I regret with this girl,

16:54.767 --> 16:57.100
but I wasn't the perfect
boyfriend or any of that.

16:57.133 --> 16:58.667
-Have you had
anything to drink today?

16:58.700 --> 17:00.867
-Uh, way earlier this morning,
but I've been asleep.

17:00.900 --> 17:02.333
-Way earlier?
-Yeah.

17:02.367 --> 17:03.867
-Okay.

17:03.900 --> 17:05.467
I can still smell
the alcohol on you.

17:05.500 --> 17:07.667
Did you spill some
on your clothes?

17:07.700 --> 17:09.433
-Um, maybe in the process.
I don't know.

17:09.467 --> 17:11.200
-Oh, okay.
-I've changed clothes

17:11.233 --> 17:13.333
since I drank earlier today.
-Oh, okay.

17:13.367 --> 17:15.367
Have you ever done
a field sobriety test before?
-Yes, sir.

17:15.400 --> 17:17.767
-Okay. Keep your feet together
and your hands by your side.

17:17.800 --> 17:19.667
Just put them by your side,
not behind your back.

17:19.700 --> 17:21.900
and just follow my finger
with your eyes
and your eyes only, okay?

17:21.933 --> 17:23.133
-Yes, sir.

17:31.367 --> 17:33.500
-Perfect. Thank you.
You're good. You can lean back.

17:34.833 --> 17:37.133
-Well, we pulled this guy over
for the way he was driving.

17:37.167 --> 17:39.400
He seemed like he was
in a hurry, or...

17:39.433 --> 17:41.100
just something
didn't seem quite right.

17:41.133 --> 17:43.967
He was making a lot of
traffic violations, so we...

17:44.067 --> 17:45.933
stopped him, and then he just...

17:47.267 --> 17:49.933
keeps talking and talking
like he's real nervous

17:49.967 --> 17:51.333
or, like, something else
was going on.

17:51.367 --> 17:52.633
So he told us
we could search the car.

17:52.667 --> 17:54.433
I'm not finding
anything so far, but...

17:55.500 --> 17:57.333
maybe he just has a lot to say.

17:57.367 --> 17:58.767
-...going to work, because--
-Yes, sir.

17:58.800 --> 18:01.900
Hey, man, I know y'all meet
so many different personalities.

18:01.933 --> 18:03.500
Every time I go
to the store, dude,

18:03.533 --> 18:05.400
I see all these
weird-ass people,

18:05.433 --> 18:06.767
and they're always
asking for money.

18:06.800 --> 18:09.200
